# Copy to .env and fill in. .env is gitignored — keep it that way.
# The web app deliberately reads NO environment variables. Everything here is worker-side only,
# and none of it is required to see the demo: web/public/demo.json is committed, so
# `cd web && npm install && npm run dev` renders all five views with no keys set at all.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Needed to run the live collectors / verifiers (not needed for the demo)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Tavily — external verification of claims about entities ALREADY INDEXED on the public web
# (market comparables, prior funding rounds). Not used for receipt fetches: our fixture pages
# are hours old and a search index has never crawled them. Receipts use a direct httpx GET.
TAVILY_API_KEY=tvly-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# LLM — structured-output extraction and claim typing only.
# The model never emits a score and never writes prose; scoring is closed-form so that
# leave-one-out attribution stays exact.
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Override the local SQLite ledger path. Read by worker/db.py; defaults to db/counterproof.db.
# Useful for running a throwaway ledger without touching the seeded one.
# COUNTERPROOF_DB=db/counterproof.db

# USPTO Open Data Portal — the flagship sourcing channel (self-filed trademarks).
# Registration needs identity verification that can take hours, so the daily bulk XML committed
# as a dated fixture is the primary path, not the fallback. Not on the critical path.
# USPTO_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Not needed. Listed so nobody goes looking for them.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Supabase — NOT required to run anything, and deliberately unused at runtime. The local SQLite
# ledger at db/counterproof.db is the store. db/schema.sql is written in a Postgres-compatible
# subset purely so it can be pasted into the Supabase SQL editor to show the append-only ledger.
#
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY in particular should stay empty: an anon key is the credential a *browser*
# would use, and the frontend has zero client-side database access by design. Needing this key
# would mean the architecture had drifted.
# SUPABASE_URL=
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=
